VL  - 15
IS  - 3
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper presents the theoretical foundations for a new approach to integer programming. On the basis of the theoretical arguments, various specific computational procedures are developed which could be used to solve the integer programming problem. However, definitive computational results are not presented. In future papers we plan to explore the various computational options developed here.
AB  - This paper presents the theoretical foundations for a new approach to integer programming. On the basis of the theoretical arguments, various specific computational procedures are developed which could be used to solve the integer programming problem. However, definitive computational results are not presented. In future papers we plan to explore the various computational options developed here.
